{
  "_doc": "Magic: The Gathering—FINAL FANTASY (FIN) Play + Collector recipes from Wizards' 'Collecting FINAL FANTASY' article (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-final-fantasy). FIN has Play + Collector Boosters and NO Draft Booster (authoritative). Set codes: FIN = main set, FCA = FINAL FANTASY Through the Ages bonus sheet, FIC = FINAL FANTASY Commander, TFIN = tokens, AFIN = Art Series. cardCount includes the token/art card. Approximations: 'borderless woodblock' and 'borderless character' treatments fold into the 'borderless' filter; FINAL FANTASY artist cards approximated with the main set + 'borderless' / plain rarity. Re-pointed to named finishes per the article: Surge Foil Borderless Character cards now use the 'surge_foil' filter (article: 'Surge foil ... borderless character cards'), the generic Surge Foil mythic chase uses 'surge_foil', and the Colorful Chocobo chase uses 'neon_ink' (article: 'colorful neon ink foil Traveling Chocobo cards'). The serialized golden chocobo stays on the 'serialized' filter (no distinct Scryfall finish predicate for it). AUDIT 2026-06 (article re-verification): Through the Ages was 33.3% per common SUB-PULL (≈2.3 FCA cards per pack); the article says one-third of PLAY BOOSTERS get one → 4.76%/slot, split by the published sheet rates (U 63.25 / R 29.75 / M 7). Wildcard’s merged 16.7% rare/mythic now splits 14.3/2.4 (mythics were unreachable). Collector Booster-Fun C/U outcomes gained the borderless filter (they previously pulled regular prints). Cid-variant sub-rates not modeled (no distinguishing Scryfall tag).",
